                    "description": "\u2022\tGovernmental representative at the following Responsible Business Conduct (RBC) agreements:\n- Pension sector\n- Insurance sector (deputy)\n\n\u2022\tTransparency & reporting:\n- Negotiation and national implementation of the agreed Corporate Sustainability Reporting Directive (CSRD);\n- Member of the Governmental Advisory Group of the Global Reporting Initiative (GRI).\n\n\u2022\tEU Corporate Sustainability Due Diligence Directive (CSDDD):\n- Negotiation at EU-level of the proposed CSDDD;\n- National alignment with other departments and other (EU) legislation such as the CSRD, Taxonomy Regulation and SFDR.\n\n\u2022\tResponsible for various RBC research projects and policy themes, amongst other:\n- Monitoring on the 90% goal of the Dutch government. By 2023, 90% of large companies in the Netherlands (approx. 700+) should adhere to the OECD Guidelines (and/or UNGPs) for their international activities;\n- Revision of the Dutch National Action Plan (NAP) on Business & Human Rights;\n- Research projects as part of the roll out of the new RBC policy, a.o. research into the regulatory burden of due diligence legislation for Dutch companies.\n\n\u2022 Responsible for expanding the Theory of Change (ToC) for the Dutch RBC policy:\n- Developing sub-ToCs for the various policy instruments under the Dutch RBC policy;\n- Set up a coherent ToC, including a monitoring approach for the evaluation of the Dutch RBC policy. \n\n\u2022 Intern coach:\n- Coaching our team intern;\n- Responsible for recruiting and selecting new interns.",
